                    _t('Stanza Form and Argument Structure', 'Stanza divisions create structural units that correspond to steps in the poem\'s argument; shifts in stanza length, form, or rhyme scheme signal shifts in the poem\'s thinking, tone, or perspective.', 'Not all stanzas are equal — a shorter stanza at the poem\'s end (a couplet, a tercet) often carries disproportionate rhetorical and thematic weight; structural shifts signal conceptual shifts.', 'FRQ: explain how a specific stanza break or change in stanza form contributes to the poem\'s development of its central idea.'),
