                    _t('Irony in Poetry', 'Verbal irony says one thing while meaning another (including sarcasm); situational irony creates contrast between expectation and reality; dramatic irony creates contrast between what the speaker knows and what the reader understands; all three can operate in poems simultaneously.', 'Irony in poetry is not just sarcasm — the most significant poetic irony is often structural (the poem\'s form contradicts its content) or dramatic (the reader sees what the speaker cannot).', 'FRQ: explain how a specific form of irony functions in a poem to create complexity or advance the central idea.'),
