                    ('Treating a literary work as a "unified statement" means:', ['Analyzing how all elements work together to create a coherent, complex meaning rather than cataloging separate devices', 'Arguing that every element in the work is equally important', 'Finding the single sentence that states the work\'s central idea', 'Analyzing the work chronologically from beginning to end']),
