                    _t('AP® Lit Exam Structure', 'The AP® Literature exam has two sections: Section I — 55 multiple-choice questions in 60 minutes (prose and poetry passages with comprehension, analysis, and interpretation questions); Section II — 3 FRQs in 2 hours (FRQ 1: prose analysis, FRQ 2: poetry analysis, FRQ 3: literary argument).', 'Students often underestimate the MC section — it requires careful close reading of prose and poetry passages under time pressure; practicing timed close reading is as important as practicing FRQ writing.', 'Practice: complete a full timed AP® Literature MC section; analyze which question types (inference, tone, figurative language, structure) are most challenging.'),
